# HALE-BOPP — Cursor/AI Agent Rules
# "Su HALE-BOPP puntiamo sempre in alto e non dobbiamo essere paurosi."
# Deterministic data tools. No AI inside. Pure mechanics.

# Project Identity
# HALE-BOPP is an open-source (Apache 2.0) suite of deterministic data tools:
#   - hale-bopp-db:    Schema governance engine (PostgreSQL)
#   - hale-bopp-etl:   Config-driven data orchestration (YAML pipelines)
#   - hale-bopp-argos: Policy gating & data quality engine
# Org: https://github.com/hale-bopp-data

# Language & Stack
# Python 3.10+, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Docker Compose
# No AI/ML dependencies inside the tools — deterministic by design

# Repository Structure
# This is a monorepo with 3 independent modules:
#   db/    — hale-bopp-db    (port 8100)
#   etl/   — hale-bopp-etl   (port 3001 webhook, watcher)
#   argos/ — hale-bopp-argos (port 8200)
#   docs/  — shared documentation
# Each module has its own pyproject.toml, Dockerfile, tests/, CI workflow

# Branch Strategy
# 2-tier: feat→main (no develop branch)
# Branch prefixes: feat/, fix/, docs/, test/, refactor/, chore/
# Commit convention: Conventional Commits — type(scope): description
#   Types: feat, fix, docs, test, refactor, chore
#   Scopes: db, etl, argos, docs, ci

# PR Rules
# - All PRs target `main`
# - Tests must pass (CI runs pytest on every PR)
# - No hardcoded values (connection strings, passwords, paths)
# - PR description explains WHY, not just WHAT
# - Reference issue number if applicable

# Code Style
# - Follow existing patterns — read the code before writing new code
# - Type hints on public functions
# - Docstrings on public API (modules, classes, public functions)
# - pytest for testing — meaningful coverage, not vanity metrics
# - Config via environment variables or YAML, never hardcoded

# Security
# - Hardcoded secrets = immediate revert
# - Connection strings via DATABASE_URL env var
# - Docker: pin versions, least privilege, no root
# - Secrets scan runs on every PR (GitHub Actions)

# API Contracts
# The 3 modules communicate via a Universal Event Schema.
# See API_CONTRACTS.md for the contract that ties them together.
# Breaking changes to the event schema require updating ALL 3 modules.

# Testing
# Each module runs independently:
#   cd db && pytest tests/ -v
#   cd etl && pytest tests/ -v
#   cd argos && pytest tests/ -v
# db tests require PostgreSQL (Docker Compose or CI service container)

# Philosophy
# "Muscles" — deterministic, no AI, pure mechanics.
# The tools do exactly what you tell them, nothing more.
# Reliability over cleverness. Simplicity over features.
